{
  "stem": "1581.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But somehow, he feverishly cut off the sleeves of the boots, so that there was only the shoe left.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And there-- he held on to the shoes for dear life.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And later on, we only realized why he did that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "When the SS saw what he had done, they beat him half to death because he ruined some boots that they could have used.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But somehow, he held onto his shoes and could use them, and we only learned much later why he was almost giving his life to hold on to those shoes.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But I come to this later.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "We finally were given this uniform and clothes, and we were to marched back to our barracks.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "The barracks were just plain misery.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "There were, again, these three-tiered sleeping arrangements, with cubicles barely enough for four people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "We had to sleep 10 of them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "In order to sleep, we had to sleep on our sides, because we couldn't stretch out on our backs.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "There was absolutely no food.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "As we learned later, our blockalteste, or kapo, of course received our rations, if you want to call it, pieces of bread and some soup.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "But he knew that our stay there will not be very long, and we are doomed anyway, so he sold our rations for himself, and we were left hungry.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And we--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, this kapo-- all the kapos in-- in Birkenau were criminals, which were marked by a yellow-- by a red triangle.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had yellow triangles.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were political prisoners who had a green triangle.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were all marks so you knew which one-- and the Jew, of course, had to have a-- a Jew-- a Juden on it in addition.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was not a group.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Just this one guy, and he was quite a guy.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
